criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  1. Snoring or apneas objectively observed during sleep by a partner;

  2. Symptoms that are potentially secondary to apneas/hypopneas with an intermediate-high
     probability of being treated with CPAP. In operative terms, Epworth scale ≥12 or
     previous cardiovascular disease;

  3. Age between 18 and 70 years;

  4. Absence of any clinical suspicion of any other sleep pathology susceptible to
     coinciding with daytime sleepiness.

Exclusion Criteria:

  1. Psycho-physical incapacity to complete questionnaires;

  2. Documented structural or coronary heart disease uncontrolled by any medical
     treatment;

  3. Cheyne-Stokes syndrome;

  4. Patients subjected to uvulopalatopharyngoplasty;

  5. Significant nasal obstruction impeding the use of CPAP;

  6. Pregnancy;

  7. Lack of informed consent.
